The "User denied account access" error occurs when a user rejects the connection request from your application in the MetaMask wallet.

To handle this error, you can add a try-catch block when requesting the account access from MetaMask and show an appropriate error message to the user. Add the try-catch block around `await window.ethereum.enable()` or `await window.ethereum.request({ method: 'eth_requestAccounts' })` in your `useEffect` hook:

```javascript
useEffect(() => {
  const loadWeb3AndContract = async () => {
    if (window.ethereum) {
      try {
        // Request account access from MetaMask
        await window.ethereum.enable(); // or await window.ethereum.request({ method: 'eth_requestAccounts' })

        // Load web3
        const web3Instance = new Web3(window.ethereum);
        setWeb3(web3Instance);

        // Load the user's account address
        const accounts = await web3Instance.eth.getAccounts();
        setAccount(accounts[0]);

        // Load the contract instance
        const contractInstance = new web3Instance.eth.Contract(contractABI, contractAddress);
        setContract(contractInstance);

      } catch (error) {
        alert('Please allow access to your MetaMask wallet to continue');
      }
    } else {
      alert('Please install and connect MetaMask to continue');
    }
  };

  loadWeb3AndContract();
}, []);
```

Now, if the user denies account access, your application will show an alert message requesting the user to allow access. This will help users understand that they need to grant account access for your application to work correctly.

